article.headline: Marist 34, Bryant 7
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Chris Debowski threw for a career-high 321 yards and tied a school record with four touchdown passes to lead Marist to a 34-7 victory over Bryant on Saturday. Debowski connected with James LaMacchia on an 80-yard touchdown pass on the Red Foxes' first possession, and the offense never slowed down. Marist (2-5) led 13-0 at halftime before Debowski hooked up with LaMacchia for a second time for a 55-yard touchdown pass with 5:03 left in the third quarter. LaMacchia finished with four catches for 154 yards and two touchdowns for the Red Foxes, who snapped a three-game losing streak. Lindsey Gamble's 7-yard touchdown run for Bryant (3-3) cut the deficit to 27-7 with 10:52 left in the game. The Red Foxes answered with a 25-yard touchdown reception by freshman R.J. Roe with 7:49 remaining. Roe caught four passes for 66 yards and had two scores for Marist.
